---------------------------------------------------------<br>
First, I'd like to preface this message by saying that I have not heard of, or witnessed, any members of the Knights of Valor conducting themselves in a way that is contrary to our Charter.<br>
<br>
With any business or company, it is always great to see growth because it usually means that goals, revenue and hopefully profitability are moving in the right direction. So it is with the Knights of Valor. Lately we have seen our numbers increase, an i'm sure it's because of the "name" we've created for ourselves. We've created our name / reputation by our actions as individuals and as a guild. But with growth, it is common to forget what made us successful in the first place, and with the increase of our numbers, now may be a good time (as individuals and Knights of Valor) to revisit it.<br>
First it starts with our leadership. I must say "hats off" to our Officers. I believe they all have shown themselves to be genuinely concerned about the members of the Knights of Valor, and have conducted themselves in a way that is an example for the rest of us to follow. From Ryland running across Norrath to bring me an item, to Langley helping port me for a quest, to Slaydark bringing a piece of armor for Humma at Highkeep. The examples are endless and too deep to list them all. Now, saying that, we should also keep in mind to respect the time of the Officers as they also are enjoying their expereience. But they are always there to help and answer questions.<br>
As far as conduct, the only thing I'd like to say, is to remember that your actions and words are not just a reflection of you, but you are also representing me,...and Ryland, and Slaydark, and Colins, and Moksoon, and all of the Knights of Valor. I feel that above all-else, we must protect the integrity of our guild, the Knights of Valor, and be deligent in doing so. I went back and re-read our Charter, its outstanding. If you hacen't done so in a while, please re-read it. Particulary to our newer members.<br>
The meaning of this message is not to define our conduct. That has been done (quite well) in our Charter, but to share my perspective and the hope that we all are aware of the work involved in maintaining a cohesive family. It is always great to see everybody welcome a member when they log on, or saying Goodbye when someone leaves. It's the little things...its in the deatil...It reminds me of a management philosophy called Kaizen-meaning Continuous Improvement. Just think of the little old gaardener working in this big beautiful garden, and he is busy pruning one little branch.It's not the one little branch that he's pruning that makes the big garden beautiful, but all the little branches,on a whole,that was improved in the process.<br>
So it must be within our guild, to continuously improve the relationships between ourselves. Always remember "the little things". <br>
As for me personally, I'd like to let you all know that I'm kind of playful when I'm playing Longbow and enjoy joking around and looking for humor in situtations. Please don't ever take offense to anything I may say. I would never say anything disparaging to any member of the Knights of Valor. When I call Seiyan "The Crazy Monk", its all in good fun and jest, and is not to be taken as a lack of respect. Not that anybody has ever complained, but I tend to be animated in my communication using hands, face and hands, tone,and emotion, and all that can be hard to translate into static words. For example, I love talking to Colins because he and I joke around a lot. He hammers me about being a weak Ranger,and I hammer away at everything that is wrong with a Warrior...heheh (actually I like him because he's so big, in a fight I can hide behind him or hang on to one of his legs!)<br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope this wasn't too long, but I felt that our maintaining our honor and integrity as a guild should not be forgotten or taken for granted. I DO NOT think that it has been in jeopaardy, but we must be proactive in maintaining the "reasons" on what made us successful in the first place.<br>
Thanks for the ear...<br>
<br>
Longbow <br>
<br>
Longbow<br>
Knight of Valor<br>
Animo et Fide!!<br>
